00:09:32.980 --> 00:09:36.440
and I had mixed feelings when
I heard that we were going

00:09:36.440 --> 00:09:39.030
to play the Mozart because
Mozart does it so well.

00:09:39.030 --> 00:09:41.040
[ Laughter ]

00:09:41.040 --> 00:09:44.390
And, but that's okay.

00:09:44.390 --> 00:09:45.690
Okay.

00:09:45.690 --> 00:09:46.990
&gt;&gt; David Plylar: Well one thing

00:09:46.990 --> 00:09:48.290
about your title is I've
always thought that you,

00:09:48.290 --> 00:09:52.150
you had a little certain sense of
humor similar to Milton Babbitt

00:09:52.150 --> 00:09:54.410
